The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 October is 84,077 (9,690.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 October, there were 3,080 new confirmed cases (355.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 October, there were 2,405 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 28% (675 extra cases).
